abstract: House passes bill approving construction of Keystone XL oil pipeline, measure that passed Senate in January; Pres Obama has promised to veto measure, and two-thirds majority necessary to override veto is not expected.
lead_paragraph: While most congressional Republicans and some Democrats supported the Keystone pipeline, the measure is not expected to draw the two-thirds majority necessary to override a veto.

headline.main: House Passes Keystone Bill Despite Obama’s Opposition
headline.print_headline: House Passes Bill Approving the Keystone Pipeline, but a Veto Is Expected

snippet: While most congressional Republicans and some Democrats supported the Keystone pipeline, the measure is not expected to draw the two-thirds majority necessary to override a veto.
